<title>USA: Avant gets $4.5 mln Rockwell contract.</title>
<headline>Avant gets $4.5 mln Rockwell contract.</headline>
<dateline>SUNNYVALE, Calif 1997-03-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Avant Corp said Monday the semiconductor unit of Rockwell International Corp bought $4.5 million of its software for chip design.</p>
<p>Rockwell Semiconductor Systems will use Avant's products to make next-generation chips for modems, fax machines, cordless telephones and other communication devices, the companies said.</p>
<p>Avant, based in Sunnyvale, Calif, writes computer programs that help electrical engineers design computer chips.</p>
